cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the security of infrastructure systems and uses game theory to model the interaction between the defender and attacker. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Among these, cs.CR and cs.GT are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the paper's focus on security and game theory.
